deftms ~>>>FACE 'faces of a 3D mesh treated by hashing i.e. 
the position of a face is the sum of its vertex numbers if this place is free
else the position is obtained by a chaining on the next face
and boundary faces are also chained'
variable muet DATE 'date of creation of the TMS'   reel2  ;
variable muet NUTD 'number of the descriptor array TD' entier ; 
variable MOFACE 'number of integers stored for each face(>=8)' entier ;
variable MXFACE 'max number of faces'                entier ;        
variable L1FAFR 'number of the first boundary face'  entier ; 
variable NBFAFR 'number of boundary faces'           entier ;
variable L1FA2M 'number of the first interface face' entier ; 
variable NBFA2M 'number of interface faces'          entier ;
variable NBFATG 'number of faces with tangents'      entier ;
tableau  LFACES(1..MOFACE,1..MXFACE)
'4 vertices,link,fe1,fe2 or next boundary face, face with tangents' entier ;
tableau  NUTGFA(1..8,1..NBFATG) 'numbers of tangents of faces' entier ;
fintms ;
         

For memory :
NBFATG=0 signifies that the tangents array does not exist
NBSTFA=0 signifies that the coordinates array does not exist

For a SURFACE or a VOLUME, MOFACE>=8 (no type of the FE).
For an OBJECT (and NOT for a PLSV), the subroutine hachob adds 
at position 9 of LFACES the type (1 to NBTYEL) of the last FE
of the object containing the face 
=> the face interpolation is fixed and MOFACE>=9 for an OBJECT
